  <p>
    Proper post-treatment care is crucial for maximizing the benefits of your regenerative medicine procedure 
    and ensuring optimal healing. Following these guidelines will help support your body's natural healing 
    process and minimize potential complications.
  </p>

  <h2>Immediate Post-Treatment (First 24 Hours)</h2>
  <p>During the first 24 hours after your treatment:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Rest and avoid strenuous activities</li>
    <li>Apply ice to the treatment area for 15-20 minutes every 2-3 hours if recommended</li>
    <li>Take prescribed medications as directed</li>
    <li>Keep the injection site clean and dry</li>
    <li>Monitor for any unusual symptoms or reactions</li>
    <li>Stay well-hydrated by drinking plenty of water</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Activity Guidelines</h2>

  <h3>First 48 Hours</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Avoid heavy lifting (over 10 pounds)</li>
    <li>No strenuous exercise or high-impact activities</li>
    <li>Limit prolonged sitting or standing</li>
    <li>Gentle walking is encouraged for circulation</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>First Week</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Gradually resume normal daily activities</li>
    <li>Avoid intense exercise until cleared by your physician</li>
    <li>No massage or manipulation of the treatment area</li>
    <li>Continue gentle movement and stretching as tolerated</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>After One Week</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Resume normal exercise routine gradually</li>
    <li>Listen to your body and avoid activities that cause pain</li>
    <li>Follow up with your physician as scheduled</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Medication and Supplement Guidelines</h2>
  <p>To support healing and avoid interference with treatment:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Pain Management</strong>: Use acetaminophen (Tylenol) for pain relief instead of NSAIDs</li>
    <li><strong>Avoid NSAIDs</strong>: No ibuprofen, naproxen, or aspirin for 7-10 days post-treatment</li>
    <li><strong>Supplements</strong>: Avoid fish oil and vitamin E for 5-7 days</li>
    <li><strong>Prescribed Medications</strong>: Continue all prescribed medications unless instructed otherwise</li>
    <li><strong>Anti-inflammatory Medications</strong>: Only use if specifically prescribed by your physician</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Injection Site Care</h2>
  <p>Proper care of the injection site promotes healing and prevents infection:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Keep the area clean and dry for 24 hours</li>
    <li>Avoid soaking in baths, hot tubs, or swimming pools for 48 hours</li>
    <li>Gentle showering is permitted after 4-6 hours</li>
    <li>Do not apply lotions, creams, or makeup to the injection site for 24 hours</li>
    <li>Avoid direct pressure or massage of the area</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What to Expect</h2>

  <h3>Normal Reactions</h3>
  <p>The following are normal and expected after treatment:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Mild soreness or stiffness at the injection site</li>
    <li>Slight swelling or bruising</li>
    <li>Temporary increase in pain (may last 24-72 hours)</li>
    <li>Fatigue or feeling run down</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Timeline for Improvement</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>1-3 days</strong>: Initial inflammation and discomfort</li>
    <li><strong>1-2 weeks</strong>: Gradual reduction in symptoms</li>
    <li><strong>4-6 weeks</strong>: Significant improvement typically begins</li>
    <li><strong>3-6 months</strong>: Maximum benefits usually achieved</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Nutrition and Hydration</h2>
  <p>Support your healing with proper nutrition:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Drink plenty of water (8-10 glasses daily)</li>
    <li>Eat anti-inflammatory foods (leafy greens, berries, fatty fish)</li>
    <li>Ensure adequate protein intake for tissue repair</li>
    <li>Limit processed foods and excessive sugar</li>
    <li>Consider vitamin D and omega-3 supplements as recommended</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Treatment-Specific Instructions</h2>

  <h3>PRP Therapy Aftercare</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Expect initial inflammation as part of the healing process</li>
    <li>Avoid anti-inflammatory medications that may interfere with healing</li>
    <li>Follow activity restrictions carefully to protect the treated area</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Exosome Therapy Aftercare</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Monitor injection site for any unusual reactions</li>
    <li>Follow standard post-injection care protocols</li>
    <li>Report any concerns to your healthcare provider promptly</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>IV Therapy Aftercare</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Continue hydration throughout the day</li>
    <li>Monitor the IV site for any signs of irritation</li>
    <li>Resume normal activities as tolerated</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>When to Contact Your Physician</h2>
  <p><strong>Call immediately if you experience:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Severe or worsening pain that doesn't respond to acetaminophen</li>
    <li>Signs of infection (fever, increased redness, warmth, or discharge)</li>
    <li>Allergic reactions (rash, difficulty breathing, swelling)</li>
    <li>Numbness or tingling that persists</li>
    <li>Any symptoms that cause significant concern</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Follow-Up Care</h2>
  <p>
    Regular follow-up appointments are essential to monitor your progress and adjust treatment plans as needed. 
    Attend all scheduled appointments and communicate openly about your recovery experience.
  </p>

